  "doc_id": "31346",
  "text": "According to what has been previously reported, analysis of paired samples in chronic phase MPN vs. MPN-BP has clearly demonstrated that more than one signaling pathway is associated with leukemic transformation. In addition, JAK2-mutated chronic phase disease transformed into JAK2-mutated MPN-BP in some patients, whereas in other cases the JAK2 mutation was not detected further [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Accordingly, the transforming event which leads to AML could occur in a pre-JAK2-mutated ancestral clone, or chronic phase MPN could be biclonal from its outset.",
